          h1 Code-mixing and Language Identification
        section
          h2 Code-mixing, switching
          ul
            li Extremely common in multilingual communities, especially online (3.5% of all tweets)
            li Code-mixing: Matrix language with insertions from other languages (often English)
            li Code-switching: changing between languages
            li Loanwords: words from other languages (understandable to speakers without knowledge of the other language)
        section
          h2 Challenges for code-mixed language
          ul
            li Lack of data; most text is from noisy sources
            li Many combinations of languages
            li How to apply monolingual trained models to code-mixed texts?
        section
          h2 Methods for code-mixed language
          ul
            li Supervised learning (from scratch)
            li Divide-and-conquer
            li Translate to matrix language
            li Zero-shot approach
